  "sections": [
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Editor’s note: We are proud to publish this major investigative report today from journalist Steve Horn. As you’ll see, California may be a blue state, but the fossil fuel industry still has enormous power in the state’s politics. — Sirota"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "This report was written by Steve Horn."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      0
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Big money from Big Oil and industry-tied unions has helped to kill a legislative effort to create environmental protections for communities living near oil and gas operations in California."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "On August 5, a 5-4 Senate committee vote "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            1
          ],
          1,
          "struck down consideration"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " of legislation calling for consideration of a 2,500-foot setback between future oil wells and homes, schools and playgrounds. Only one of those votes came from a Republican."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "It was the second time in as many years that the bill -- "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            2
          ],
          1,
          "Assembly Bill 345"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " -- failed to pass, and it failed to do so even after several rounds of significant amendments had watered down the legislation. With that, a years-long activist-led legislative movement went up in smoke for 2020."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "And then came the "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            3
          ],
          1,
          "historically large wildfires"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ". Within a matter of days, the state’s northern half caught fire at an epic scale, wildfires made worse from climate change and fueled by unfettered fossil fuel drilling. California oil is "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            4
          ],
          1,
          "some of the dirtiest"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", from a climate change perspective, in the United States."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Drilling for oil in the state also has major public health repercussions, an impetus driving AB 345. Recent studies have linked oil drilling in California to health impacts, including "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            5
          ],
          1,
          "low birth weight and small gestational age"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", as well as preterm births. Research has also linked "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            6
          ],
          1,
          "higher levels of industrial pollution"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " to higher contraction rates of COVID-19."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Despite these impacts, the bill attracted a core group of Democratic legislators who ultimately oversaw the bill’s demise. Three of those who spoke out the most strongly against AB 345 at the Senate Committee on Natural Resources and Water hearing on August 5 before voting against it -- Sen. Ben Hueso, Sen. Andreas Borgeas and Senate Majority Leader Bob Hertzberg -- have received high dollar contributions and other support from oil interests that lobbied against AB 345."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The lobbying and influence campaign efforts waged by the oil industry and labor against AB 345 illustrates the difficulty in crafting climate policy and environmental protections -- even in a state with a super-majority Democratic Party legislature that bills itself as a global leader on fighting climate change."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "A big part of the difficulty is the contradiction of the center of it all: California is the "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            7
          ],
          1,
          "sixth biggest oil producer"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " nationwide and the "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            8
          ],
          1,
          "largest west coast oil refiner"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h4",
      [
        [
          0,
          [
            9
          ],
          1,
          "Exxon Backdoor?"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "When he spoke out on the Senate floor against AB 345 before voting it down, Hueso called the legislation a “waste of time” and “publicity stunt” by environmental justice groups. Termed out of the legislature after having served in both the Assembly and Senate, he is now running for the San Diego County Board of Supervisors District 1 seat."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Campaign financial disclosure data for that race shows that the East Los Angeles-area lobbying firm Urban Associates Inc. "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            10
          ],
          1,
          "donated $90,000"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " before the March 3 primary to an independent expenditure committee supporting Hueso and a committee that opposed one of his primary opponents."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Prime Strategies, the firm that owns Urban Associates, has "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            11
          ],
          1,
          "lobbied"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " for ExxonMobil since 2017. ExxonMobil has accounted for roughly 60 percent of the firm’s California revenue. In the first quarter of 2020, Prime Strategies listed AB 345 as the sole piece of legislation on which it "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            12
          ],
          1,
          "lobbied"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " at the state-level."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "“Urban Associates, Inc. is a longtime supporter of Senator Ben Hueso,” Katherine Hennigan, a spokesperson for the firm, said via email. “Our company believes he is a strong advocate for good paying, union jobs and working families. To suggest anything more than that is simply insulting and another example of politics at its worst.”"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "ExxonMobil spokeswoman Ashley Alemayehu told TMI the company had “no involvement in Sen. Hueso’s local campaign.”"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Democrat Nora Vargas, Hueso’s general election opponent in the race, had sharp words on the vote."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "“Instead of voting to protect California families and children from the health impacts of oil and gas drilling, Senator Hueso has once again failed our communities and the over 5 million Californians -- mostly black, indigenous, and people of color -- who live in a mile of drilling sites,” said Vargas."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "During his state legislative career, Hueso has received "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            13
          ],
          1,
          "$27,300"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " in campaign contributions from companies that lobbied against AB 345."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Hueso also has "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            14
          ],
          1,
          "behested"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " tens of thousands of dollars from the fossil fuel industry throughout his political career, including $30,000 from the Western State Petroleum Association, $35,000 from Chevron, $15,000 from Phillips 66 and $1,000 from BP. Behesting is when California politicians raise money from outside groups or corporations and then donate it to other nonprofits, which some have described as another "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            15
          ],
          1,
          "avenue of influence peddling"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Hueso’s legislative office and campaign team did not respond to multiple requests for comment for this story."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h4",
      [
        [
          0,
          [
            9
          ],
          1,
          "Labor-Oil Alliance"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Urban Associates donated to another Democratic lawmaker who helped derail AB 345. Fellow San Diegan Lorena Gonzalez, who serves as Chair of the Assembly Appropriations Committee and Legislative Latino Caucus, received a "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            16
          ],
          1,
          "$5,000 contribution"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " from the firm on April 25 last year for her campaign for Secretary of State in 2022."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The donation came just three weeks before Gonzalez tabled AB 345 until the 2020 session and four days before the appropriations committee introduced "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            17
          ],
          1,
          "heavy amendments"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " into the legislation. The chair of the committee has unilateral power to table legislation for the second year of a session or kill it altogether."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "A month after she tabled AB 345 for the 2019 session, Gonzalez received another "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            18
          ],
          1,
          "$4,700 campaign contribution"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " from Chevron for her 2020 Assembly race. About two weeks after killing the bill for 2019, Gonzalez received a "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
